#Text=The Sacramento Kings ( 21 - 37 ) defeated the New York Knicks ( 12 - 47 ) 124 - 86 on Tuesday at Madison Square Garden in New York .
#Text=The Kings dominated this game offensively right from the beginning , out - scoring the Knicks 65 - 39 by half , and reaching the 100 - point mark after just the third quarter .

#Text=Their superior shooting was a big reason for this , as they went 49 percent from the field and 56 percent from the three - point line , while the Knicks finished at 37 percent from the floor and just 18 percent from deep .
#Text=Along with that , the Kings also secured a 46 - 38 rebounding advantage , only furthering their impressive performance Tuesday .
#Text=The Kings saw six players reach double figures in this one , along with three reaching the 20 - point plateau .

#Text=Rudy Gay led the way , going 9 - for - 15 from the field and 3 - for - 4 from the three - point line to score a team - high of 25 points , to go along with seven rebounds and four assists in just 26 minutes .
#Text=He 's now shot 40 percent or higher in each of his last four games , a span where he 's averaging 23 points and 7 rebounds .
#Text=DeMarcus Cousins also was a big factor in the win , finishing with 22 points ( 5 - 10 FG , 1 - 1 3Pt , 11 - 11 FT ) , 10 rebounds and two blocked shots .
#Text=Like Gay , he 's been a beast lately , averaging 24 points and 11 rebounds over his last five games .
#Text=Both players could have put up some even higher numbers in this matchup , but because of the blowout , they were each held to less than 30 minutes on the court .
#Text=Ben McLemore was also very efficient with his time , scoring 20 points ( 6 - 12 FG , 2 - 4 3Pt , 6 - 7 FT ) in just 23 minutes .
#Text=He 's picked up his game of late , recording two 20 - point games over his last three , despite averaging just 12 points on the season .
#Text=Coming off the bench , Derrick Williams and Nik Stauskas reached double figures as well with 17 and 15 points respectively .
#Text=As shown by their final score , the Knicks struggled to get much going Tuesday , including having all five of their starters combine for just 24 points .
#Text=With that being said , they did see some solid contributions off their bench .
#Text=Alexey Shved led the team in scoring , posting 15 points ( 4 - 11 FG , 0 - 4 3Pt , 7 - 9 FT ) , to go along with seven rebounds and three assists in 32 minutes .
#Text=It was a season - high in minutes for the guard , as he took advantage of the extra time with his second 15 - point showing in a row .
#Text=Shane Larkin was also one of those bench players who provided some points .
#Text=He went 5 - for - 9 from the field and 1 - for - 3 from the three - point line to finish with 13 points , while adding six assists and two steals as well .
#Text=It was just the sixth time all season that he finished in double - digit points .
#Text=The only other Knick to reach double figures was Jason Smith , who posted 13 points ( 6 - 10 FG , 0 - 1 3Pt , 1 - 2 FT ) , four rebounds and three blocked shots in 21 minutes .
#Text=The Kings ' next game will be on the road against the San Antonio Spurs on Wednesday , while the Knicks will travel to Indiana to play the Pacers on Wednesday .
